ra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hugues","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Hugues Capet  (  ?938–96 ) was ruler of France (  987–96 ) and founder of the Capetian dynasty.  See  <b>Hugh</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Hugues I de Brienne Comte de Brienne was born in 1235, in Brienne-le-Château, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, France, his father, Gautier IV de Brienne Comte de Brienne, de Jaffa et d’Ascalon, was 30 and his mother, Marie de Lusignan, was 11232. He married Isabella de la Roche Comtesse de Brienne et Duchesse d'Athènes in 1272. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died on 9 August 1296, in Gagliano Castelferrato, Enna, Sicily, Italy, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1235–9 August 1296":"1235–9. august 1296","1235–1296":"1235–1296","1240–1261":"1240–1261","1250–1291":"1250–1291","1235–Female":"1235–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1275–1311":"1275–1311","1275–Female":"1275–Surnud","1205–1246":"1205–1246","1215–1251":"1215–1251","5 juillet 1251":"5. juuli 1251","1275":"1275","1296":"1296","1251":"1251","1240":"1240","1272":"1272","1250":"1250","1261":"1261","1291":"1291","1205":"1205","1215":"1215","1235":"1235","1246":"1246","1311":"1311","1233":"1233","Abt 1275":"umbes 1275","9 August 1296":"9. august 1296","Bef 1291":"enne 1291","Le Caire, Égypte":"Káhira, Egiptus","Gagliano Castelferrato, Enna, Sicily, Italy":"Gagliano Castelferrato, Enna, Sicilia, Itaalia","Chypre":"Küpros","Brienne-le-Château, Aube, Champagne-Ardenne, France":